This article is a transcript of President Biden's remarks at Raleigh-Durham International Airport in Durham, North Carolina. The President discussed various topics including gun control, the situation in Israel, his concerns about democracy in Israel, his interactions with the families of Nashville shooting victims, and his plans to visit Nashville and Mississippi. He also mentioned his concerns about the banking crisis, terrorism threat in Northern Ireland, and the need for regulatory reform. Additionally, President Biden expressed his support for an assault weapon ban and criticized the influence of money in politics.